.TH SSHPILOT 1 "July 2026" "sshpilot 5.6.4" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
sshpilot \- SSH connection manager with integrated terminal
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sshpilot
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sshPilot
is a GTK4/libadwaita SSH connection manager with an integrated VTE terminal,
port forwarding and tunnelling, and an SFTP file manager. It stores connection
profiles, integrates with the system keyring for credentials, and drives the
native OpenSSH client for every connection.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-verbose ", " \-v
Verbose debug logging (overrides config).
.TP
.BR \-\-quiet ", " \-q
Only show warnings and errors (overrides config).
.TP
.B \-\-isolated
Use an isolated SSH configuration.
.TP
.B \-\-log\-gtk\-warnings
Also capture lower-severity GTK/GLib info and debug messages.
.TP
.B \-\-fatal\-warnings
Abort on the first GTK/GLib warning or critical, writing a full backtrace to
crash.log.
.TP
.B \-\-diagnostics
Shorthand for \fB\-\-verbose \-\-log\-gtk\-warnings\fR. Recommended when filing
a bug report.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.ssh/config
The OpenSSH client configuration, which sshPilot treats as the source of truth
for per-host settings.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR ssh (1),
.BR ssh_config (5)
